title: For Sale:  Ruger Black Hawk 357/9mm convertible
postcontent:
Using 2 interchangeable cylinders, Ruger® Blackhawk® Convertible Single-Action Revolver allows shooters to use a wide variety of ammunition in one sidearm. In times of scarcity, the Blackhawk Convertible will function with 3 types of common handgun ammunition: 357 Magnum, 38 Special, and 9mm Luger. This is not only a great handgun for big game hunting, self-defense, and rugged outdoor adventures, but it also makes the perfect sidearm for anyone who takes being prepared for emergencies seriously. The 357/38 cylinder can be replaced by the 9mm cylinder by simply opening the loading gate, pushing on the base pin release button, and sliding the base pin forward. No tools are needed and there are no small parts to loose. 

For the Blackhawk Single-Action Revolver, Ruger incorporated the classic lines and inherent strengths of the US military service revolver used in the late 1800s with modern steel and manufacturing techniques to make the safest and most rugged sidearms made. The Blackhawk is built on a robust, all-steel frame made to withstand modern magnum cartridges, and uses all coil springs in the mechanism that retain their power for ultra-durability (instead of leaf-springs). Ruger's transfer bar ignition system provides an unparalleled measure of security against accidental discharge, allowing the shooter to carry the revolver safely with all 6 chambers loaded. The Blackhawk's traditional western-style grip is renown for being one of the most natural pointing grips ever designed, enabling shooters to instinctively draw and shoot, as well as stand and take aim. The rear sight is protected by integral frame topstrap ribs, and is click adjustable for both windage and elevation, allowing user to make precision adjustments when changing types of ammunition. The front sight is an improved Partridge type that provides a good sight picture, and allows for snag-free withdrawal from holsters. The Ruger Blackhawk Single-Action Revolver Convertible is a well-designed, reliable firearm that utilizes the widest range of ammunition of any single handgun available. Made in USA.

TangoDown LLC's new vertical grip features the next generation of life-saving utility and strength. Designed to fit any Mil-Std 1913 rail, this product can withstand punishing abuse mounted on weapon systems from the M4 Carbine to the Mk. 48 SAW.
Vertical fore grips are often called upon to mount pressure switches for lasers and tactical lights. In the past, Velcro or adhesive tape were less- than satisfactory methods of securing the pressure switch to the grip. Heat, rapid movement and heavy gloves often rip the switch loose with obvious consequences. The Tango grip features a novel pocket that appears when needed, to positively mount pressure switches without movement or damage. Just remove the threaded end cap, slide out the filler panel and place inside the grip for storage. title: For Sale:  Hand-Forged Knife by Gary Little (Conklin Meadows Forge)
postcontent:
Up for sale: an heirloom-quality skinner by Gary Little of Broadbent, Oregon, where he operates Conklin Meadows Forge.

Gary has been hand-forging knives since the 1980's - not made from mass-produced blanks, each knife is truly one-of-a-kind.  Exceptional craftsmanship by a local master!

I purchased this knife from its original owner, and I have never cut a single thing with it.  It's in as-new condition, as the original owner wore it on his belt for over twenty years but never abused it.  It would be hard to find a knife of this quality for under $300.

This sharpened portion of the (hollow-ground) blade measures 3.75" in length, with an overall knife length of 8.75".  ...blade is 3/16" wide at the backbone, which runs full-length and a full 3/16" width all the way to the pommel, which has a brass insert for a lanyard.  I can't positively ID the wood species, but I do know that it is a laminate formed under pressure.  

The blade is zonally-hardened, with the business edge somewhat softer & more ductile than the backbone, for a super-keen edge.  The backbone is tempered for higher stiffness - somewhat like the famed Nihonto a.k.a. Samurai swords, for the best balance of edge retention and superior overall durability.

The scabbard is hand-made to fit by Gary's wife, out of 1/8" thick saddle leather, and shows some nicks and scrapes from being carried/worn for so long. All stitching is intact, and the retention is perfect - it will not drop the knife when shaken upside-down, but the knife is drawn easily when needed.  

I hate to part with this piece - but bills and other interests force me to give up my little treasure.  I'm sure the lucky buyer will appreciate its beauty and workmanship, and maybe pass it on to a child or grandchild.  As Gary may not be in the hand-forged knife business for too many more years, due to age, this knife can only appreciate in value and desirability.

More pictures available upon request.

$175 Firm (reduced from $200)

(open to trades - just let me know what you have in mind - worst I can say is "No thanks!")
